preqs: LAW1100 OR LAW1101 and LAW1102 or LAW1104; LAW2100 or LAW2101 and LAW2102; LAW2200 or LAW2201 and LAW2202; LAW3400 or LAW3401 and LAW3402

rules.ruleString: Must have passed 4 (I/W) units in {LAW1100, LAW1102, LAW1104, LAW2100, LAW2102, LAW2200, LAW2202, LAW3400, LAW3402}
Must be enrolled in course owned by {50000567, 50000568}

description: This unit will provide an introduction to the new legal and social issues which have arisen due to the now extensive use of the internet for commerce, education and entertainment. The unit will cover issues such as jurisdiction, electronic contracting, electronic security, content regulation, intellectual property, privacy and will provide sufficient flexibility to examine any new issues as they arise.
